                <h1>An Overview of Frequent Urination</h1>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="">Symptoms</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|</li>
                    <li><a href="">Causes</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|</li>
                   
                    <li><a href="">Diagnosis</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|</li>
                    <li><a href="">Treatment</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|</li>
                    <li><a href="">FAQs</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;|</li>
                    
                </ul>
                <p>Frequent urination is often caused by drinking lots of liquids, especially caffeine or alcohol. If your frequent urination isn’t related to what or how much you’re drinking, it may be caused by an underlying medical condition. While it could be a simple reason, such as the medication you're taking or a urinary tract infection (UTI), it could also be a sign of a chronic condition, such as interstitial cystitis or diabetes.

                    <br><br>
                    Read on to find out more information about the causes, diagnosis, and treatment of frequent urination.</p>
